The paper deals with blind detection in wireless communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The proposed scheme involves decoding a set of candidates within a strict time constraint, which requires efficient algorithms and data structures (cs.SY and cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between different system parameters, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI).
